    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I believe I am seeing this same problem with the Ruby interop server on Linux. To reproduce it, run\n\n``` sh\nruby src/ruby/bin/interop/interop_server.rb --use_tls=true --port 7070\n```\n\n(port number arbitrarily chosen)\n\nThen run the following command twice:\n\n``` sh\ntools/run_tests/run_interop_tests.py -l node ruby c++ python csharp php --override_server ruby=localhost:7070 --use_docker -t -j 8\n```\n\nAll or almost all of the tests pass in the first run, and all of the tests time out in the second run. Using `gdb`, I can confirm that after the first run, the server has a single thread blocked on `poll` with `grpc_completion_queue_pluck` in the stack trace, and that that instance of `grpc_completion_queue_pluck` never returns. In addition, at the end of the first run of tests, the server always outputs the following log lines:\n\n```\nE1021 13:35:46.125181984   29590 handshake.c:186]            Read failed.\nE1021 13:35:46.125207022   29590 server_secure_chttp2.c:155] Secure transport failed with error 2\n```\n"
  },
